
[1]wasting

   WASTING, ppr.

   1. Lavishing prodigally; expending or consuming without use;
   diminishing by slow dissipation; desolating; laying waste.

   Wasting and relentless war has made ravages, with but few and short
   intermissions, from the days of the tyrant Nimrod down to the Nimrod of
   our own age.

   2. a. Diminishing by dissipation or by great destruction; as a wasting
   disease.
